locality: At village Bokumu ca 12 km from Goma airport, between airport and Parc National des Virunga (Sud) in grasslands in low lying drainage leading to forest margin just outside of Parc National Virunga. Region of seasonally burned grasslands.

INERA Station at Mulungu, collected ca 200 m west of Luhora village of south Mulungu in frequently grazed area along path in short grass. Restricted population under grazing pressure. Plants growing in old maize field with Carex spp., Physalis and Convolvulus. Soil of well eroded cinders and sand.
Grasslands at bottom of escarpment on new Mgololo, to Sawala road, in river valley.

Annex of Parc National des Kundelungu at site of the summer house of M. Lux near source of Lwongenge stream. Ca 25 km NE of Parc National Kundelungu along gallery forest at edge of stream at base of slope, soil fine and humusy.
11 km from John's Corner on Mufindi road, Malakala
